import Main from "../../layouts/Main.astro"
import PullQuote from "../../components/PullQuote.astro"
---

<Main title="Chats" description="My series 'Career Chats: Real conversations about careers in tech'.">
    <section id="projects">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium">üéôÔ∏è Career Chats</h2>
        <span class="text-sm text-neutral-500">Real conversations about careers in tech</span>

        <p class="mt-4">
            Career Chats is an ongoing series where I sit down with people working in tech to talk about how they actually got here - the non-linear paths, challenges along the way, and lessons they've learned.
        </p>

        <div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-2 mt-4">
            <div class="space-y-6 leading-relaxed">
                <p>
                    Breaking into tech can feel opaque. Job titles are unclear, career paths are rarely linear, and most advice focuses on outcomes rather than journeys.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Career Chats exists to make those journeys visible ‚Äî by documenting honest conversations with people at different stages of their careers and sharing what they wish they knew earlier.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="leading-relaxed">
                <p class="font-semibold">Each episode explores:</p>

                <ul class="list-disc marker:text-primary mb-4">
                    <li>What the guest does day-to-day</li>
                    <li>How they got into tech</li>
                    <li>Challenges and unexpected detours</li>
                    <li>Advice for students and early-career professionals</li>
                </ul>

                <PullQuote>
                    Episodes are short, focused, and designed to be practical.
                </PullQuote>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            <p>
                I started Career Chats as a way to learn from people I admire and to share those insights with others navigating similar decisions. Along the way, patterns start to emerge - and those patterns are often more valuable than any single piece of advice.
            </p>

            <p>
                If you're working in tech and would like to be part of the series - or if there's someone you'd like me to chat with - feel free to get in touch.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>
</Main>

